- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes an unsupervised learning approach for domain adaptation.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with machine learning techniques applied to NLP tasks.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper mentions the use of neural networks for word representation learning.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely category as the paper does not deal with image or video data, but it is still possible as the paper mentions the use of convolutional neural networks for word representation learning.
